President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Victoria Hughes as a member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service. Hughes currently serves as the Director of Development at the Ashbrook Center at Ashland University. She has previous experience in various roles, including Vice President for Development at the Reason Foundation, Executive Vice President of A.C. Fitzgerald & Associates, and Founding President and Senior Advisor at the Bill of Rights Institute. She has also held positions at the Charles G. Koch, Claude R. Lambe, Fred and Mary Koch Foundations, Koch Industries, Inc., Citizens for a Sound Economy, and the United States Information Agency. Hughes has a background in education, having worked as a classroom teacher in Cincinnati, Boston, and Washington, D.C. She holds a B.S. from the University of Dayton and currently serves on the Board of Trustees at the Thomas More College of Liberal Arts.